\section{Robustness}

{% if validation %}
{% if validation.design == "rdd" %}
The scan max-LLR was calibrated by randomization against fitted-null replicas
(+1-rank Monte Carlo p = {{ validation.p_value | texesc }}; a parametric bootstrap,
never an exact test --- audit item 1). Local intercept-continuity placebo tests over
the remaining covariates: {{ validation.placebo | texesc }}, Holm-corrected
p = {{ validation.placebo_holm | texesc }}. The density falsification test on the
signed distance along the frozen discovered normal gives
p = {{ validation.density_p | texesc }}; it is valid only for the frozen discovered
geometry --- search selection is not accounted for (audit item 6) --- and is reported
as a falsification check, not a confirmation.
{% else %}
The scan max-LLR was calibrated by randomization against fitted-null replicas of kind
``{{ validation.null_kind | texesc }}'' (+1-rank Monte Carlo
p = {{ validation.p_value | texesc }}; a parametric bootstrap, never an exact test ---
audit item 1). Composition check (pre/post unit-mix independence inside the window):
{{ validation.composition | texesc }}. Anticipation placebo jumps before $T_0$ (Holm
across shifts): {{ validation.anticipation | texesc }}. These checks replace
McCrary-in-time, which is information-free when record times are design-determined
(audit item 18).
